ُمُ","fr":"(fait) interdire vous","en":"(does) forbid you","tr":"yanhākumu","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ٱللَّهُ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-lahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"عَنِ","fr":"de","en":"from","tr":"ʿani","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"ٱلَّذِينَ","fr":"ceux qui","en":"those who","tr":"alladhīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"لَمْ","fr":"(fais) non","en":"(do) not","tr":"lam","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"يُقَـٰتِلُوكُمْ","fr":"combattre vous","en":"fight you","tr":"yuqātilūkum","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"فِى","fr":"en","en":"in","tr":"fī","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"ٱلدِّينِ","fr":"la religion","en":"the religion","tr":"l-dīni","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"وَلَمْ","fr":"et (fais) non","en":"and (do) not","tr":"walam","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"يُخْرِجُوكُم","fr":"pousser vous hors","en":"drive you out","tr":"yukh'rijūkum","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"مِّن","fr":"de","en":"of","tr":"min","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"دِيَـٰرِكُمْ","fr":"votre maisons","en":"your homes","tr":"diyārikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"أَن","fr":"que","en":"that","tr":"an","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"تَبَرُّوهُمْ","fr":"vous traitez kindly","en":"you deal kindly","tr":"tabarrūhum","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"وَتُقْسِطُوٓا۟","fr":"et agir avec justice","en":"and deal justly","tr":"watuq'siṭū","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"إِلَيْهِمْ ۚ","fr":"avec eux","en":"with them","tr":"ilayhim","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"إِنَّ","fr":"Certes","en":"Indeed","tr":"inna","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"ٱللَّهَ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-laha","isWaqf":false},{"position":20,"ar":"يُحِبُّ","fr":"aime","en":"loves","tr":"yuḥibbu","isWaqf":false},{"position":21,"ar":"ٱلْمُقْسِطِينَ","fr":"ceux qui agir avec justice","en":"those who act justly","tr":"l-muq'siṭīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":9,"verseKey":"60:9","juz":28,"arabic":"إِنَّمَا يَنْهَىٰكُمُ ٱللَّهُ عَنِ ٱلَّذِينَ قَـٰتَلُوكُمْ فِى ٱلدِّينِ وَأَخْرَجُوكُم مِّن دِيَـٰرِكُمْ وَظَـٰهَرُوا۟ عَلَىٰٓ إِخْرَاجِكُمْ أَن تَوَلَّوْهُمْ ۚ وَمَن يَتَوَلَّهُمْ فَأُو۟لَـٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلظَّـٰلِمُونَ","fr":"Allah vous défend seulement de prendre pour alliés ceux qui vous ont combattus à cause de votre religion, vous ont chassés de vos foyers ou ont aidé à votre expulsion. Ceux qui les prennent pour alliés sont eux les injustes.","en":"Allāh only forbids you from those who fight you because of religion and expel you from your homes and aid in your expulsion - [forbids] that you make allies of them. And whoever makes allies of them, then it is those who are the wrongdoers.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"إِنَّمَا","fr":"Seulement","en":"Only","tr":"innamā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"يَنْهَىٰكُمُ","fr":"interdit vous","en":"forbids you","tr":"yanhākumu","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ٱللَّهُ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-lahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"عَنِ","fr":"de","en":"from","tr":"ʿani","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"ٱلَّذِينَ","fr":"ceux qui","en":"those who","tr":"alladhīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"قَـٰتَلُوكُمْ","fr":"combattre vous","en":"fight you","tr":"qātalūkum","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"فِى","fr":"en","en":"in","tr":"fī","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"ٱلدِّينِ","fr":"la religion","en":"the religion","tr":"l-dīni","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"وَأَخْرَجُوكُم","fr":"et pousser vous hors","en":"and drive you out","tr":"wa-akhrajūkum","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"مِّن","fr":"de","en":"of","tr":"min","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"دِيَـٰرِكُمْ","fr":"votre maisons","en":"your homes","tr":"diyārikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"وَظَـٰهَرُوا۟","fr":"et soutenir","en":"and support","tr":"waẓāharū","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"عَلَىٰٓ","fr":"en","en":"in","tr":"ʿalā","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"إِخْرَاجِكُمْ","fr":"votre expulsion","en":"your expulsion","tr":"ikh'rājikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"أَن","fr":"que","en":"that","tr":"an","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"تَوَلَّوْهُمْ ۚ","fr":"vous faire eux alliés","en":"you make them allies","tr":"tawallawhum","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"وَمَن","fr":"Et quiconque","en":"And whoever","tr":"waman","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"يَتَوَلَّهُمْ","fr":"fait eux alliés","en":"makes them allies","tr":"yatawallahum","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"فَأُو۟لَـٰٓئِكَ","fr":"puis ceux","en":"then those","tr":"fa-ulāika","isWaqf":false},{"position":20,"ar":"هُمُ","fr":"[ils]","en":"[they]","tr":"humu","isWaqf":false},{"position":21,"ar":"ٱلظَّـٰلِمُونَ","fr":"(sont) les injustes","en":"(are) the wrongdoers","tr":"l-ẓālimūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":10,"verseKey":"60:10","juz":28,"arabic":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوٓا۟ إِذَا جَآءَكُمُ ٱلْمُؤْمِنَـٰتُ مُهَـٰجِرَٰتٍ فَٱمْتَحِنُوهُنَّ ۖ ٱللَّهُ أَعْلَمُ بِإِيمَـٰنِهِنَّ ۖ فَإِنْ عَلِمْتُمُوهُنَّ مُؤْمِنَـٰتٍ فَلَا تَرْجِعُوهُنَّ إِلَى ٱلْكُفَّارِ ۖ لَا هُنَّ حِلٌّ لَّهُمْ وَلَا هُمْ يَحِلُّونَ لَهُنَّ ۖ وَءَاتُوهُم مَّآ أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ وَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكُمْ أَن تَنكِحُوهُنَّ إِذَآ ءَاتَيْتُمُوهُنَّ أُجُورَهُنَّ ۚ وَلَا تُمْسِكُوا۟ بِعِصَمِ ٱلْكَوَافِرِ وَسْـَٔلُوا۟ مَآ أَنفَقْتُمْ وَلْيَسْـَٔلُوا۟ مَآ أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ ذَٰلِكُمْ حُكْمُ ٱللَّهِ ۖ يَحْكُمُ بَيْنَكُمْ ۚ وَٱللَّهُ عَلِيمٌ حَكِيمٌ","fr":"Ô vous qui avez cru ! Quand des croyantes viennent vers vous en émigrées, mettez-les à l’épreuve, car Allah en Sait mieux sur leur foi. Si vous les avez trouvées vraiment croyantes, ne les rendez pas aux (maris) mécréants. Désormais, ni elles ne seront plus licites pour eux, ni eux ne seront licites pour elles. Mais rendez-leur ce qu’ils ont dépensé (comme mahr : dot). Il n’y aura alors aucun grief contre vous si vous les épousez en leur versant (à votre tour) leur mahr (dot). De même, ne conservez pas les liens du mariage avec les mécréantes. Réclamez (à votre tour) ce que vous avez dépensé comme mahr (dot), tout comme (les maris mécréants) le réclament. Tel est le Jugement d’Allah Qui décide entre vous. Allah est Omniscient et Sage.","en":"O you who have believed, when the believing women come to you as emigrants, examine [i.e., test] them. Allāh is most knowing as to their faith. And if you know them to be believers, then do not return them to the disbelievers; they are not lawful [wives] for them, nor are they lawful [husbands] for them. But give them [i.e., the disbelievers] what they have spent. And there is no blame upon you if you marry them when you have given them their due compensation [i.e., mahr]. And hold not to marriage bonds with disbelieving women, but ask for what you have spent and let them [i.e., the disbelievers] ask for what they have spent. That is the judgement of Allāh; He judges between you. And Allāh is Knowing and Wise.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا","fr":"Ô vous","en":"O you","tr":"yāayyuhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"ٱلَّذِينَ","fr":"qui","en":"who","tr":"alladhīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ءَامَنُوٓا۟","fr":"croire","en":"believe","tr":"āmanū","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"إِذَا","fr":"Quand","en":"When","tr":"idhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"جَآءَكُمُ","fr":"venir à toi","en":"come to you","tr":"jāakumu","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"ٱلْمُؤْمِنَـٰتُ","fr":"le croyant femmes","en":"the believing women","tr":"l-mu'minātu","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"مُهَـٰجِرَٰتٍۢ","fr":"(comme) émigrants","en":"(as) emigrants","tr":"muhājirātin","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"فَٱمْتَحِنُوهُنَّ ۖ","fr":"puis examine eux","en":"then examine them","tr":"fa-im'taḥinūhunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"ٱللَّهُ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-lahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"أَعْلَمُ","fr":"(est) le mieux informeré","en":"(is) most knowing","tr":"aʿlamu","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"بِإِيمَـٰنِهِنَّ ۖ","fr":"de leur foi","en":"of their faith","tr":"biīmānihinna","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"فَإِنْ","fr":"Et si","en":"And if","tr":"fa-in","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"عَلِمْتُمُوهُنَّ","fr":"vous savoez eux","en":"you know them","tr":"ʿalim'tumūhunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"مُؤْمِنَـٰتٍۢ","fr":"(à être) croyants","en":"(to be) believers","tr":"mu'minātin","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"فَلَا","fr":"puis ne fais pas","en":"then (do) not","tr":"falā","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"تَرْجِعُوهُنَّ","fr":"retourner eux","en":"return them","tr":"tarjiʿūhunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"إِلَى","fr":"à","en":"to","tr":"ilā","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"ٱلْكُفَّارِ ۖ","fr":"les mécréants","en":"the disbelievers","tr":"l-kufāri","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"لَا","fr":"Non","en":"Not","tr":"lā","isWaqf":false},{"position":20,"ar":"هُنَّ","fr":"ils","en":"they","tr":"hunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":21,"ar":"حِلٌّۭ","fr":"(sont) licite","en":"(are) lawful","tr":"ḥillun","isWaqf":false},{"position":22,"ar":"لَّهُمْ","fr":"pour eux","en":"for them","tr":"lahum","isWaqf":false},{"position":23,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":24,"ar":"هُمْ","fr":"ils","en":"they","tr":"hum","isWaqf":false},{"position":25,"ar":"يَحِلُّونَ","fr":"sont licite","en":"are lawful","tr":"yaḥillūna","isWaqf":false},{"position":26,"ar":"لَهُنَّ ۖ","fr":"pour eux","en":"for them","tr":"lahunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":27,"ar":"وَءَاتُوهُم","fr":"Mais donner eux","en":"But give them","tr":"waātūhum","isWaqf":false},{"position":28,"ar":"مَّآ","fr":"ce que","en":"what","tr":"mā","isWaqf":false},{"position":29,"ar":"أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ","fr":"ils ont dépensa","en":"they have spent","tr":"anfaqū","isWaqf":false},{"position":30,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"Et non","en":"And not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":31,"ar":"جُنَاحَ","fr":"aucun blâme","en":"any blame","tr":"junāḥa","isWaqf":false},{"position":32,"ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ","fr":"sur vous","en":"upon you","tr":"ʿalaykum","isWaqf":false},{"position":33,"ar":"أَن","fr":"si","en":"if","tr":"an","isWaqf":false},{"position":34,"ar":"تَنكِحُوهُنَّ","fr":"vous épousez eux","en":"you marry them","tr":"tankiḥūhunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":35,"ar":"إِذَآ","fr":"quand","en":"when","tr":"idhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":36,"ar":"ءَاتَيْتُمُوهُنَّ","fr":"vous ont donné eux","en":"you have given them","tr":"ātaytumūhunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":37,"ar":"أُجُورَهُنَّ ۚ","fr":"leur (nuptial) dues","en":"their (bridal) dues","tr":"ujūrahunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":38,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"Et (fais) non","en":"And (do) not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":39,"ar":"تُمْسِكُوا۟","fr":"tenir","en":"hold","tr":"tum'sikū","isWaqf":false},{"position":40,"ar":"بِعِصَمِ","fr":"à mariage liens","en":"to marriage bonds","tr":"biʿiṣami","isWaqf":false},{"position":41,"ar":"ٱلْكَوَافِرِ","fr":"(avec) mécréant femmes","en":"(with) disbelieving women","tr":"l-kawāfiri","isWaqf":false},{"position":42,"ar":"وَسْـَٔلُوا۟","fr":"mais demander (pour)","en":"but ask (for)","tr":"wasalū","isWaqf":false},{"position":43,"ar":"مَآ","fr":"ce que","en":"what","tr":"mā","isWaqf":false},{"position":44,"ar":"أَنفَقْتُمْ","fr":"vous ont dépensa","en":"you have spent","tr":"anfaqtum","isWaqf":false},{"position":45,"ar":"وَلْيَسْـَٔلُوا۟","fr":"et laisser eux demander","en":"and let them ask","tr":"walyasalū","isWaqf":false},{"position":46,"ar":"مَآ","fr":"ce que","en":"what","tr":"mā","isWaqf":false},{"position":47,"ar":"أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ","fr":"ils ont dépensa","en":"they have spent","tr":"anfaqū","isWaqf":false},{"position":48,"ar":"ذَٰلِكُمْ","fr":"Cela","en":"That","tr":"dhālikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":49,"ar":"حُكْمُ","fr":"(est le) Jugement","en":"(is the) Judgment","tr":"ḥuk'mu","isWaqf":false},{"position":50,"ar":"ٱللَّهِ ۖ","fr":"(d') Allah","en":"(of) Allah","tr":"l-lahi","isWaqf":false},{"position":51,"ar":"يَحْكُمُ","fr":"Il juge","en":"He judges","tr":"yaḥkumu","isWaqf":false},{"position":52,"ar":"بَيْنَكُمْ ۚ","fr":"entre vous","en":"between you","tr":"baynakum","isWaqf":false},{"position":53,"ar":"وَٱللَّهُ","fr":"Et Allah","en":"And Allah","tr":"wal-lahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":54,"ar":"عَلِيمٌ","fr":"(est) Omniscient","en":"(is) All-Knowing","tr":"ʿalīmun","isWaqf":false},{"position":55,"ar":"حَكِيمٌۭ","fr":"Très-Sage","en":"All-Wise","tr":"ḥakīmun","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":11,"verseKey":"60:11","juz":28,"arabic":"وَإِن فَاتَكُمْ شَىْءٌ مِّنْ أَزْوَٰجِكُمْ إِلَى ٱلْكُفَّارِ فَعَاقَبْتُمْ فَـَٔاتُوا۟ ٱلَّذِينَ ذَهَبَتْ أَزْوَٰجُهُم مِّثْلَ مَآ أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ وَٱتَّقُوا۟ ٱللَّهَ ٱلَّذِىٓ أَنتُم بِهِۦ مُؤْمِنُونَ","fr":"Si certaines de vos femmes fuient vers les mécréants, et que, lors d’une riposte victorieuse (vous preniez possession d’un butin), donnez alors à ceux que leurs femmes ont fuis, (prélevé sur ce butin), le mahr (dot) qu’ils avaient versé. Et craignez Allah en Qui vous croyez.","en":"And if you have lost any of your wives to the disbelievers and you subsequently obtain [something], then give those whose wives have gone the equivalent of what they had spent. And fear Allāh, in whom you are believers.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"وَإِن","fr":"Et si","en":"And if","tr":"wa-in","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"فَاتَكُمْ","fr":"ont parti de vous","en":"have gone from you","tr":"fātakum","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"شَىْءٌۭ","fr":"tout","en":"any","tr":"shayon","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"مِّنْ","fr":"de","en":"of","tr":"min","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"أَزْوَٰجِكُمْ","fr":"votre épouses","en":"your wives","tr":"azwājikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"إِلَى","fr":"à","en":"to","tr":"ilā","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"ٱلْكُفَّارِ","fr":"les mécréants","en":"the disbelievers","tr":"l-kufāri","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"فَعَاقَبْتُمْ","fr":"puis votre se détourner vient","en":"then your turn comes","tr":"faʿāqabtum","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"فَـَٔاتُوا۟","fr":"puis donner","en":"then give","tr":"faātū","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"ٱلَّذِينَ","fr":"(à) ceux qui","en":"(to) those who","tr":"alladhīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"ذَهَبَتْ","fr":"ont parti","en":"have gone","tr":"dhahabat","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"أَزْوَٰجُهُم","fr":"leur épouses","en":"their wives","tr":"azwājuhum","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"مِّثْلَ","fr":"(le) comme","en":"(the) like","tr":"mith'la","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"مَآ","fr":"(de) ce que","en":"(of) what","tr":"mā","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"أَنفَقُوا۟ ۚ","fr":"ils avait dépensa","en":"they had spent","tr":"anfaqū","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"وَٱتَّقُوا۟","fr":"Et crains","en":"And fear","tr":"wa-ittaqū","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"ٱللَّهَ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-laha","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"ٱلَّذِىٓ","fr":"(dans) Que","en":"(in) Whom","tr":"alladhī","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"أَنتُم","fr":"vous","en":"you","tr":"antum","isWaqf":false},{"position":20,"ar":"بِهِۦ","fr":"[dans Lui]","en":"[in Him]","tr":"bihi","isWaqf":false},{"position":21,"ar":"مُؤْمِنُونَ","fr":"(sont) croyants","en":"(are) believers","tr":"mu'minūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":12,"verseKey":"60:12","juz":28,"arabic":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلنَّبِىُّ إِذَا جَآءَكَ ٱلْمُؤْمِنَـٰتُ يُبَايِعْنَكَ عَلَىٰٓ أَن لَّا يُشْرِكْنَ بِٱللَّهِ شَيْـًٔا وَلَا يَسْرِقْنَ وَلَا يَزْنِينَ وَلَا يَقْتُلْنَ أَوْلَـٰدَهُنَّ وَلَا يَأْتِينَ بِبُهْتَـٰنٍ يَفْتَرِينَهُۥ بَيْنَ أَيْدِيهِنَّ وَأَرْجُلِهِنَّ وَلَا يَعْصِينَكَ فِى مَعْرُوفٍ ۙ فَبَايِعْهُنَّ وَٱسْتَغْفِرْ لَهُنَّ ٱللَّهَ ۖ إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ غَفُورٌ رَّحِيمٌ","fr":"Ô Prophète ! Quand les croyantes, par un serment d’allégeance, viennent jurer devant toi qu’elles n’associeront rien à Allah, qu’elles ne voleront point, ne commettront point la fornication, ne tueront point leurs enfants, n’attribueront pas mensongèrement (à leurs maris des enfants adultérins), ni ne te désobéiront en ce qui est convenable, alors accepte leur allégeance, et implore pour elles le pardon d’Allah, car Allah est Absoluteur et Tout Miséricordieux.","en":"O Prophet, when the believing women come to you pledging to you that they will not associate anything with Allāh, nor will they steal, nor will they commit unlawful sexual intercourse, nor will they kill their children, nor will they bring forth a slander they have invented between their arms and legs, nor will they disobey you in what is right - then accept their pledge and ask forgiveness for them of Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا","fr":"Ô","en":"O","tr":"yāayyuhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"ٱلنَّبِىُّ","fr":"Prophète","en":"Prophet","tr":"l-nabiyu","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"إِذَا","fr":"Quand","en":"When","tr":"idhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"جَآءَكَ","fr":"venir à toi","en":"come to you","tr":"jāaka","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"ٱلْمُؤْمِنَـٰتُ","fr":"le croyant femmes","en":"the believing women","tr":"l-mu'minātu","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"يُبَايِعْنَكَ","fr":"pledging à vous","en":"pledging to you","tr":"yubāyiʿ'naka","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"عَلَىٰٓ","fr":"[sur]","en":"[on]","tr":"ʿalā","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"أَن","fr":"que","en":"that","tr":"an","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"لَّا","fr":"non","en":"not","tr":"lā","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"يُشْرِكْنَ","fr":"ils va associer","en":"they will associate","tr":"yush'rik'na","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"بِٱللَّهِ","fr":"avec Allah","en":"with Allah","tr":"bil-lahi","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"شَيْـًۭٔا","fr":"quoi que ce soit","en":"anything","tr":"shayan","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"يَسْرِقْنَ","fr":"ils va steal","en":"they will steal","tr":"yasriq'na","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"يَزْنِينَ","fr":"ils va commettre adultère","en":"they will commit adultery","tr":"yaznīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"يَقْتُلْنَ","fr":"ils va tuer","en":"they will kill","tr":"yaqtul'na","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"أَوْلَـٰدَهُنَّ","fr":"leur enfants","en":"their children","tr":"awlādahunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":20,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":21,"ar":"يَأْتِينَ","fr":"ils apportent","en":"they bring","tr":"yatīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":22,"ar":"بِبُهْتَـٰنٍۢ","fr":"calomnie","en":"slander","tr":"bibuh'tānin","isWaqf":false},{"position":23,"ar":"يَفْتَرِينَهُۥ","fr":"ils inventent cela","en":"they invent it","tr":"yaftarīnahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":24,"ar":"بَيْنَ","fr":"entre","en":"between","tr":"bayna","isWaqf":false},{"position":25,"ar":"أَيْدِيهِنَّ","fr":"leurs mains","en":"their hands","tr":"aydīhinna","isWaqf":false},{"position":26,"ar":"وَأَرْجُلِهِنَّ","fr":"et leur pieds","en":"and their feet","tr":"wa-arjulihinna","isWaqf":false},{"position":27,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"et non","en":"and not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":28,"ar":"يَعْصِينَكَ","fr":"ils va désobéir vous","en":"they will disobey you","tr":"yaʿṣīnaka","isWaqf":false},{"position":29,"ar":"فِى","fr":"en","en":"in","tr":"fī","isWaqf":false},{"position":30,"ar":"مَعْرُوفٍۢ ۙ","fr":"(le) droit","en":"(the) right","tr":"maʿrūfin","isWaqf":false},{"position":31,"ar":"فَبَايِعْهُنَّ","fr":"puis accepter leur engagement","en":"then accept their pledge","tr":"fabāyiʿ'hunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":32,"ar":"وَٱسْتَغْفِرْ","fr":"et demander pardon","en":"and ask forgiveness","tr":"wa-is'taghfir","isWaqf":false},{"position":33,"ar":"لَهُنَّ","fr":"pour eux","en":"for them","tr":"lahunna","isWaqf":false},{"position":34,"ar":"ٱللَّهَ ۖ","fr":"(de) Allah","en":"(from) Allah","tr":"l-laha","isWaqf":false},{"position":35,"ar":"إِنَّ","fr":"Certes","en":"Indeed","tr":"inna","isWaqf":false},{"position":36,"ar":"ٱللَّهَ","fr":"Allah","en":"Allah","tr":"l-laha","isWaqf":false},{"position":37,"ar":"غَفُورٌۭ","fr":"(est) Pardonneur","en":"(is) Oft-Forgiving","tr":"ghafūrun","isWaqf":false},{"position":38,"ar":"رَّحِيمٌۭ","fr":"Très-Miséricordieux","en":"Most Merciful","tr":"raḥīmun","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":13,"verseKey":"60:13","juz":28,"arabic":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُوا۟ لَا تَتَوَلَّوْا۟ قَوْمًا غَضِبَ ٱللَّهُ عَلَيْهِمْ قَدْ يَئِسُوا۟ مِنَ ٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ كَمَا يَئِسَ ٱلْكُفَّارُ مِنْ أَصْحَـٰبِ ٱلْقُبُورِ","fr":"Ô vous qui avez cru ! Ne prenez pas pour alliés des gens qui ont provoqué contre eux la colère d’Allah, qui désespèrent de l’autre monde, comme les mécréants désespèrent (du retour à la vie) de ceux qui sont dans les tombes.","en":"O you who have believed, do not make allies of a people with whom Allāh has become angry. They have despaired of [reward in] the Hereafter just as the disbelievers have despaired of [meeting] the companions [i.e., inhabitants] of the graves.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا","fr":"Ô vous","en":"O you","tr":"yāayyuhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"ٱلَّذِينَ","fr":"qui","en":"who","tr":"alladhīna","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ءَامَنُوا۟","fr":"croire","en":"believe","tr":"āmanū","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"لَا","fr":"(Ne) fais pas","en":"(Do) not","tr":"lā","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"تَتَوَلَّوْا۟","fr":"faire alliés","en":"make allies","tr":"tatawallaw","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"قَوْمًا","fr":"(de) un peuple","en":"(of) a people","tr":"qawman","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"غَضِبَ","fr":"(le) colère","en":"(The) wrath","tr":"ghaḍiba","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"ٱللَّهُ","fr":"(d') Allah","en":"(of) Allah","tr":"l-lahu","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ","fr":"(est) sur eux","en":"(is) upon them","tr":"ʿalayhim","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"قَدْ","fr":"Certes","en":"Indeed","tr":"qad","isWaqf":false},{"position":11,"ar":"يَئِسُوا۟","fr":"ils désespoent","en":"they despair","tr":"ya-isū","isWaqf":false},{"position":12,"ar":"مِنَ","fr":"de","en":"of","tr":"mina","isWaqf":false},{"position":13,"ar":"ٱلْـَٔاخِرَةِ","fr":"l'Au-delà","en":"the Hereafter","tr":"l-ākhirati","isWaqf":false},{"position":14,"ar":"كَمَا","fr":"comme","en":"as","tr":"kamā","isWaqf":false},{"position":15,"ar":"يَئِسَ","fr":"désespoir","en":"despair","tr":"ya-isa","isWaqf":false},{"position":16,"ar":"ٱلْكُفَّارُ","fr":"les mécréants","en":"the disbelievers","tr":"l-kufāru","isWaqf":false},{"position":17,"ar":"مِنْ","fr":"de","en":"of","tr":"min","isWaqf":false},{"position":18,"ar":"أَصْحَـٰبِ","fr":"(le) compagnons","en":"(the) companions","tr":"aṣḥābi","isWaqf":false},{"position":19,"ar":"ٱلْقُبُورِ","fr":"(de) le tombes","en":"(of) the graves","tr":"l-qubūri","isWaqf":false}]}]